en_484543_0	A group of private bus employees carried out demonstrations in several locations across the country citing several demands.
en_484543_1	A strike was carried out in Bastian Mawatha, Pettah which is the bus stop for private buses operating on long haul routes.
en_484543_2	Protesters demand that immediate solutions must be given to the 11 demands that they have put forth.
en_484543_3	Employees charge that they have held numerous discussions with relevant government officials however no solution has been provided.
en_484543_4	Employees also noted that they dislike wearing the uniform given to them and burnt uniforms in protest.
en_484543_5	Passengers from several areas across the country were severely inconvenienced due to protests conducted by private bus employees.
en_484543_6	News1stt cameras captured the manner in which SLTB buses were provided to avoid the inconvenience the passengers would have to face.
en_484543_7	Minister of internal transport Ranjith Maddumabandara, criticising the actions of the private bus employees, noted that they should not inconvenience the passengers and that this strike action is unfair.
